From a8e057abe3a26baca32962313b430927bfd25de9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Florent Revest <revestflo@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 30 Apr 2026 12:57:38 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Explicitly make hwcomposer a shared library

Without TEMPLATE/CONFIG overrides, load(qt_plugin) wouldn't build a
real .so under Qt6 with our toolchain. Setting TEMPLATE = lib +
CONFIG += plugin shared forces qmake to emit a shared library, but
also bypasses the qt_plugin INSTALLS scaffolding, so qmake's generated
Makefile ends up with an empty install target. Add an explicit
target.path / INSTALLS pair so `make install` actually drops
libhwcomposer.so into $$[QT_INSTALL_PLUGINS]/platforms.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate
---
 hwcomposer/hwcomposer.pro | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/hwcomposer/hwcomposer.pro b/hwcomposer/hwcomposer.pro
index 0885ee2..6afb409 100644
--- a/hwcomposer/hwcomposer.pro
+++ b/hwcomposer/hwcomposer.pro
@@ -4,6 +4,10 @@ PLUGIN_TYPE = platforms
 PLUGIN_CLASS_NAME = QEglFShwcIntegrationPlugin
 load(qt_plugin)
 load(configure)
+TEMPLATE = lib
+CONFIG += plugin shared
+target.path = $$[QT_INSTALL_PLUGINS]/platforms
+INSTALLS += target

 INCLUDEPATH += .
 DEPENDPATH += .
